rek of 20 km from Kedarnath to Sonprayag. The vehicles wait for you in Sonprayag Car Parking and you\'ll drive to your hotel. Overnight at Guptkashi, (Nala).'),(288,136,'Day 8: Guptakashi - Padukeshwar',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Drive to Badrinath via Joshimath.Check in Hotel. Later at evening visit Badrinath. Overnight stay at hotel in Pandukeshwar.'),(289,136,'Day 9: Padukeshwar - Badrinath - Rudraprayag / Srinagar',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','After Breakfast early morning Time 7 Am we will drive to Badrinath. Badrinath: one of the \'Four Dhams\' is one of the most celebrated pilgrimage spots of the country and is situated at an elevation of 3,133 meters, guarded on either side by the two mountain ranges known as Nar & Narayan with the towering Neelkanth Peak providing a splendid backdrop. This revered spot was once carpeted with wild berries. Thus the place got the name Badrivan, meaning forest of berries.Overnight stay at hotel in Rudraprayag.'),(290,136,'Day 10: Rudraprayag / Srinagar - Rishikesh ',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Early morning, after breakfast, you drive downhill to Rishikesh a spiritual city and the Yoga capital of the world. your last lap of this ChardhamYatra journey. On reaching Haridwar. Sightseeing: - Visit Ram Jhula and LaxmanJhula.  Included: Drive back to Rishikesh . On Arr. Rishkesh , transfer to Railway Station / Hotel . Tour Terminate.'),(291,137,'Day 6: Guptkashi - Kedarnath',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Morning drive to Sonprayag, Trek start from Sonprayag to Kedarnath (3584 mts) on foot or on by pony/Doli, Tour members should carry personal medicines, heavy woolen, toiletries and clothes for an. Check in Hotel. Overnight at Kedarnath. Kedarnath: The Kedarnath shrine, one of the 12 Jyotirlinga of Lord Shiva, is a scenic spot situated, against the backdrop of the majestic Kedarnath range. Kedar is another name of Lord Shiva, the protector and the destroyer. According to legend, the Pandavas after having won over the Kaurava in the Kurukshetra war, felt guilty of having killed their own brothers and sought the blessings of Lord Shiva for redemption. He eluded them repeatedly and while fleeing took refuge at Kedarnath in the form of a bull. On being followed he dived into the ground, leaving his hump on the surface. The remaining portions of Lord Shiva appeared at four other places and are worshipped there as his manifestations. The arms appeared at Tungnath, the face at Rudranath, the belly at Madhmaheshwar and his locks (hair) with head at Kalpeshwar. Kedarnath and the four above-mentioned shrines are treated as PanchKedar. KEDARNATH STAY ARRANGE BY OWN. Kedarnath Trekking: Approximate Price For Pony:- Rs. 2200 - 3200/- Per Person Approximate Price For Doli:- Rs. 4000 - 6000/- Per Person Approximate Price Helicopter Fare -- Rs.7500 **/ per person Upto 80 Kg. (Rate May Be Change) Sightseeing: - visit Kedarnath Temple.'),(292,137,'Day 7: Kedarnath - Sonprayag - Guptakashi',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Early morning you get up before dawn and after taking bath you are at the temple by 4:45 am for the Abhishek\' to Kedarnath Shiva. Everyone can go inside GarbhaGriha and touch the idol. You can also prostrate with your head touching the deity etc. After darshan and puja you come out of the temple and return to the Govt. Camps / Lodges. Later you\'ll start the return trek of 20 km from Kedarnath to Sonprayag. The vehicles wait for you in Sonprayag Car Parking and you\'ll drive to your hotel. Overnight at Guptkashi, (Nala).'),(293,137,'Day 8: Guptakashi - Padukeshwar',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Drive to Badrinath via Joshimath.Check in Hotel. Later at evening visit Badrinath. Overnight stay at hotel in Pandukeshwar.'),(294,137,'Day 9: Padukeshwar - Badrinath - Rudraprayag / Srinagar',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','After Breakfast early morning Time 7 Am we will drive to Badrinath. Badrinath: one of the \'Four Dhams\' is one of the most celebrated pilgrimage spots of the country and is situated at an elevation of 3,133 meters, guarded on either side by the two mountain ranges known as Nar & Narayan with the towering Neelkanth Peak providing a splendid backdrop. This revered spot was once carpeted with wild berries. Thus the place got the name Badrivan, meaning forest of berries.Overnight stay at hotel in Rudraprayag.'),(295,137,'Day 10: Rudraprayag / Srinagar - Rishikesh - Haridwar',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 14:58:02','2025-03-26 15:56:33','Early morning, after breakfast, you drive downhill to Rishikesh a spiritual city and the Yoga capital of the world. your last lap of this ChardhamYatra journey. On reaching Haridwar. Sightseeing: - Visit Ram Jhula and LaxmanJhula.  Included:'),(310,140,'Day 1 : Delhi to Haridwar (209 km 5h approx.)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 16:11:40','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Meet and greet at Delhi railway station/ bus stand or Indira Gandhi International Airport, after that, you will be transferred to Haridwar. The holy city of God welcomes you. On arrival check into the hotel and get refreshed. After freshening up now it’s time for Ganga aarti. Drive to Har – ki – Pauri and enjoy the spiritual atmosphere at Ganga aarti. After the aarti drives back to the hotel. Now it’s time to have some dinner. After dinner, your overnight stay will be at the hotel.'),(311,140,'Day 2 : Haridwar to Barkot (177.5 km 5h 56m approx.)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 16:11:40','2025-03-26 15:55:48','After having breakfast check out from the hotel for your journey to holy Shrine. After the Check out you will be transferred to Barkot. On Route you will enjoy the mesmerizing fall i.e. Kempty falls of Mussoorie. On arrival at Barkot you will check into the hotel. After getting fresh and relaxed you will have your dinner in Hotel only. End your day by overnight stay in Hotel.'),(312,140,'Day 3 : Barkot to Yamunotri dham to Barkot (46.4km 2h 14m approx.)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 16:11:40','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Wake up and enjoy your spiritual morning in the lap of nature. Get refresh and have morning breakfast in the hotel and get ready to visit the one holy shrine among the four holy shrine of Uttarakhand. Drive to Janki chatti and from there your adventures trek of 6 Kms stars which will take you to yamunotri Dham . Visit the temple situated at the starting point of river Yamuna. After darshan you will trek back to Jnaki Chatti and from there you will be derived back to the hotel in Barkot. Get refreshed and have your dinner in a hotel. Overnight stay at hotel.'),(313,140,'Day 4 : Barkot to Rishikesh (165 km 6h 30m approx.)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-06 16:11:40','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Drive to Rishikesh, and this area hence firth came to be known as Rishikesh.  Check in Hotel. Later visit Rishikesh Temples & Sight Seeing – Laxman Jhulla, Ram Jhulla, Triveni Ghat, Bharat Mandir, Shivananda Ashram. At evening visit Ganga Aarti at Parmarth Ashram. Overnight stay.'),(314,140,'Day 5 : Rishikesh – Hardwar – Delhi (250kms/5-6hr)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-07 01:49:14','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Drive back to Delhi. On Arr. Delhi, transfer to Railway Station / Airport. Tour Terminate.'),(319,148,'Day 1: Dehradun → Barkot (via Mussoorie)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Distance: ~130 km  Travel Time: 5-6 hours  Itinerary: Morning:  Start early (around 6-7 AM) from Dehradun.  Enroute, enjoy a short stop at Mussoorie (optional), visit Kempty Falls.  Continue drive towards Barkot via Yamuna Bridge.  Afternoon:  Lunch at a roadside dhaba (plenty available on the route).  Reach Barkot by afternoon or early evening.  Evening:  Check-in at hotel/guesthouse in Barkot.  Rest & acclimatize.  Explore local markets or relax by Yamuna river.  Stay: Barkot (many budget & mid-range hotels available)'),(320,148,'Day 2: Barkot → Janki Chatti → Yamunotri → Barkot',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Itinerary: Early Morning:  Drive from Barkot to Janki Chatti (approx. 40-45 km, 1.5 hours).  Have breakfast at Janki Chatti.  Trek to Yamunotri:  Start trek from Janki Chatti to Yamunotri Temple (6 km one way).  Options: Trek by foot, pony, palki, or doli.  Enroute, enjoy the beautiful mountain views and hot water springs at Surya Kund.  Yamunotri Darshan:  Visit the Yamunotri Temple.  Spend some time for darshan, prasad, and dip in hot springs.  Return:  Trek back to Janki Chatti.  Drive back to Barkot by evening.  Stay: Barkot (same hotel)'),(321,148,'Day 3: Barkot → Dehradun',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Itinerary: Morning:  Breakfast at hotel.  Start return drive towards Dehradun.  Enroute:  You can take a short break at Kempty Falls (if skipped earlier) or Lal Tibba in Mussoorie.  Optional lunch at Mussoorie.  Evening:  Reach Dehradun by late afternoon or early evening.'),(322,149,'Day 1: Haridwar → Barkot (Approx. 180 km / 6-7 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  Depart early from Haridwar (around 6-7 AM).  Breakfast en route at Mussoorie or Kempty Falls.  Scenic drive via Mussoorie, passing by beautiful mountain views.  Afternoon:  Reach Barkot, a charming hill town, by late afternoon.  Check-in at hotel/guesthouse.  Rest & relax after the drive.  Evening:  Visit the Yamuna River banks in Barkot.  Dinner at the hotel & early rest.'),(323,149,'Day 2: Barkot → Yamunotri → Barkot (Approx. 90 km drive + 12 km trek round trip)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  Early morning drive (approx. 1.5-2 hrs) to Janki Chatti.  Begin 6 km trek to Yamunotri temple (pony/palki available if needed).  Visit Yamunotri Temple & take a dip in the Surya Kund (hot water spring).  Darshan of Goddess Yamuna.  Afternoon:  Trek back down to Janki Chatti.  Return drive to Barkot.  Evening:  Rest at Barkot.  Optional: Explore local market, interact with locals.  Dinner & overnight stay.'),(324,149,'Day 3: Barkot → Haridwar (Approx. 180 km / 6-7 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  After breakfast, check out and begin return journey.  Optional stop at Kempty Falls or Mussoorie Mall Road for a break.  Afternoon:  Lunch en route.  Reach Haridwar by evening (4-6 PM).'),(325,150,'Day 1: Rishikesh → Barkot (Approx. 170 km / 6-7 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  Start early from Rishikesh (around 6 AM) to avoid traffic.  Breakfast en route at Chamba or Tehri (beautiful views of Tehri Lake).  Afternoon:  Reach Barkot by noon/early afternoon.  Check-in at hotel/homestay. Rest & lunch.  Evening:  Explore Barkot town & Yamuna River bank.  Prep for next day’s trek.  Stay: Barkot (plenty of budget & mid-range hotels available).'),(326,150,'Day 2: Barkot → Janki Chatti → Yamunotri Trek → Return to Barkot',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  Early morning drive to Janki Chatti (approx. 45 km / 1.5 hrs).  Begin Yamunotri trek (6 km one way).  Options: Walk, pony, palki, or doli services available.  Visit Yamunotri Temple, take dip in Surya Kund (hot springs).  Perform darshan & rituals.  Afternoon:  Lunch at Janki Chatti after returning.  Drive back to Barkot (reach by evening).  Stay: Barkot (same hotel, relax after trek).'),(327,150,'Day 3: Barkot → Rishikesh Return (Approx. 170 km / 6-7 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:45:07','2025-03-26 15:55:48','Morning:  After breakfast, start return journey.  Optional halt at Kempty Falls (Mussoorie detour) if interested.  Afternoon/Evening:  Reach Rishikesh by late afternoon or evening.  Relax at Ganga ghats or attend Ganga Aarti at Triveni Ghat (optional).'),(328,46,'Day 1: Delhi → Haridwar/Rishikesh (220-240 km, 5-6 hrs drive)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:54:56','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Start early from Delhi (by 6 AM) to avoid city traffic.  En route: Breakfast stop at Moolchand Parantha or Giani Da Dhaba.  Afternoon: Reach Haridwar or Rishikesh by noon.  Visit Har Ki Pauri for Ganga Aarti (Haridwar) or Triveni Ghat (Rishikesh).  Explore Ram Jhula, Laxman Jhula, or local cafes in Rishikesh.  Night Stay: Haridwar or Rishikesh.'),(329,46,'Day 2: Haridwar/Rishikesh → Uttarkashi (170-180 km, 6-7 hrs drive)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:54:56','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Depart after breakfast.  Scenic Drive: Enjoy views along the Ganga & Bhagirathi rivers.  Pit Stops:  Chamba: Good tea/snack break.  Tehri Dam Viewpoint.  Evening: Reach Uttarkashi.  Visit Kashi Vishwanath Temple.  Explore the local market.  Night Stay: Uttarkashi.'),(330,46,'Day 3: Uttarkashi → Gangotri (100 km, 3-4 hrs drive)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:54:56','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Leave early for Gangotri.  En route visit:  Harsil Valley (apple orchards & river views).  Bhairon Ghati Bridge.  Noon: Arrive at Gangotri Temple.  Take darshan, perform puja, and spend time near Ganga’s origin.  Visit Surya Kund, Pandav Gufa if time permits.  Evening: Return to Uttarkashi (or if preferred, stay at Gangotri).  Night Stay: Uttarkashi or Gangotri (depending on accommodation availability).'),(331,46,'Day 4: Uttarkashi → Rishikesh/Haridwar (170-180 km, 6-7 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:54:56','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Start post-breakfast.  Optional Detours:  Prakateshwar Mahadev Cave Temple near Uttarkashi.  Evening: Reach Rishikesh/Haridwar.  Relax, maybe do river rafting (if time & interest allow).  Night Stay: Rishikesh or Haridwar.'),(332,46,'Day 5: Rishikesh/Haridwar → Delhi (220-240 km, 5-6 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 10:54:56','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Attend early morning Ganga Aarti (optional).  After Breakfast: Start drive back to Delhi.  Evening: Reach Delhi by evening (~6 PM).'),(333,65,'Day 1: Haridwar → Uttarkashi / Harsil (Approx. 200-220 km, 8-9 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:11:30','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Start early (by 6-7 AM) from Haridwar.  Breakfast stop at Rishikesh or Shivpuri.  On the Way: Drive via Chamba – Tehri Dam – Dharasu Bend.  Stop for lunch at Chinyalisaur or Uttarkashi.  Quick visit to Vishwanath Temple, Uttarkashi (optional).  Evening: Reach Harsil Valley (~25 km before Gangotri), known for scenic beauty OR halt at Uttarkashi.  Check-in at hotel/guesthouse.  Relax by the river, explore local area.'),(334,65,'Day 2: Harsil/Uttarkashi → Gangotri → Back to Harsil/Uttarkashi (100-120 km round trip)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:11:30','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Early morning drive to Gangotri (25-50 km, 1.5-2 hrs).  Visit Gangotri Temple, take a holy dip in Bhagirathi River.  Optional short trek to Pandav Gufa or Surya Kund.  Midday: Lunch at Gangotri town (basic dhabas available).  Spend time soaking in the beauty and spirituality.  Evening: Return to Harsil/Uttarkashi by evening.  Bonfire and dinner at your hotel/guesthouse.'),(335,65,'Day 3: Uttarkashi/Harsil → Haridwar (200-220 km, 8-9 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:11:30','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Morning: Start after breakfast.  Optional stop at Tehri Lake for quick views/photos.  Afternoon: Lunch en route at Chamba/Rishikesh.  Evening: Reach Haridwar by evening (~5-6 PM).'),(336,66,'Day 1: Rishikesh → Uttarkashi (Night Halt)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Distance: ~170 km Time: 6-7 hours  Plan: Morning: Start early (~6-7 AM) from Rishikesh.  Route: Rishikesh → Chamba → Dharasu → Uttarkashi  Stops:  Devprayag (Quick stop for the confluence view of Alaknanda & Bhagirathi)  Chamba (Tea/snack break with beautiful views)  Dharasu Bend (good viewpoint)  Evening: Reach Uttarkashi by evening.  Visit Kashi Vishwanath Temple.  Overnight stay in Uttarkashi (many hotels & guesthouses).'),(337,66,'Day 2: Uttarkashi → Gangotri → Uttarkashi (Night Halt)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Distance: ~100 km (one-way) Time: 3-4 hours one way  Plan: Start early morning (~6 AM) towards Gangotri.  Enjoy scenic drive via Harsil Valley & Bhairon Ghati.  Reach Gangotri Temple by late morning.  Darshan & explore:  Gangotri Temple  Ganga River origin point  Walk to Pandava Gufa if time permits.  Short walk near Surya Kund & Gauri Kund waterfalls.  Afternoon: After lunch, drive back to Uttarkashi.  Evening relaxation.'),(338,66,'Day 3: Uttarkashi → Rishikesh',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Distance: ~170 km Time: 6-7 hours  Plan: After breakfast, start return journey.  Stop again at scenic points like Tehri Dam viewpoint (optional).  Reach Rishikesh by evening.'),(339,67,'Day 1: Dehradun → Uttarkashi (Night Stay)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Start Early: Leave Dehradun by 6:00 AM.  Distance: ~145 km (5-6 hours drive).  Route: Dehradun → Mussoorie → Suwakholi → Chinyalisaur → Uttarkashi.  Stops:  Breakfast at Mussoorie or Suwakholi (beautiful views!).  Stop at Tehri Lake Viewpoint en route.  Reach Uttarkashi by Afternoon.  Visit Local Places:  Kashi Vishwanath Temple  Maneri Dam  Night Stay: Uttarkashi (plenty of budget/mid-range hotels).'),(340,67,'Day 2: Uttarkashi → Gangotri → Uttarkashi',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Start Early: Leave by 6:00-6:30 AM to avoid traffic & landslides.  Distance: ~100 km (3-4 hours one way).  Drive: Very scenic with river and mountain views.  En Route Stops:  Harsil Valley (apple orchards, Bhagirathi river views)  Dharali village  Gangnani (hot springs) if time permits.  Reach Gangotri Temple by late morning.  Visit Gangotri Temple, take a dip in the Bhagirathi River.  Visit Surya Kund & Pandava Gufa.  Optional small trek: Bhojbasa (partial) or Gomukh trek start point (but only if you\'re fit & have time).  Lunch at Gangotri or Harsil.  Return to Uttarkashi by evening.  Night Stay: Same hotel in Uttarkashi.'),(341,67,'Day 3: Uttarkashi → Dehradun',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:23:14','2025-03-26 15:54:22','Start: After breakfast (~8:00 AM).  Distance: ~145 km.  Option 1: Direct return to Dehradun by afternoon (4-5 hrs).  Option 2 (if relaxed):  Stop at Mussoorie for lunch and sightseeing (Kempty Falls, Mall Road).  Reach Dehradun by evening (~6:00 PM).'),(342,68,'Day 1: Delhi → Haridwar / Rishikesh (220 km, 5-6 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: Early morning start from Delhi by car/train/bus.  Afternoon: Reach Haridwar or Rishikesh.  Activities: Visit Har Ki Pauri (Haridwar) or Laxman Jhula, Ram Jhula (Rishikesh), attend Ganga Aarti in the evening.  Stay: Overnight at Haridwar/Rishikesh.'),(343,68,'Day 2: Haridwar → Guptkashi / Sonprayag (210 km, 8-9 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: Depart early, enjoy the scenic drive through Devprayag, Rudraprayag.  Afternoon: Lunch en route.  Evening: Reach Guptkashi or Sonprayag.  Stay: Overnight at Guptkashi/Sonprayag.'),(344,68,'Day 3: Guptkashi → Gaurikund → Kedarnath (Drive 30 km + Trek 16 km)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: Drive to Gaurikund, start the 16 km trek to Kedarnath (Pony/Palanquin/Helicopter options available).  Afternoon: Reach Kedarnath, visit Kedarnath Temple.  Stay: Overnight stay at Kedarnath (basic accommodation, book in advance).'),(345,68,'Day 4: Kedarnath → Guptkashi (Trek + Drive back)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: Attend early morning aarti if possible.  Trek: Descend back to Gaurikund.  Drive: Return to Guptkashi.  Stay: Overnight at Guptkashi.'),(346,68,'Day 5: Guptkashi → Rishikesh / Haridwar (210 km, 8-9 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: Drive back via Rudraprayag, Srinagar.  Evening: Reach Rishikesh/Haridwar.  Stay: Overnight stay.'),(347,68,'Day 6: Rishikesh / Haridwar → Delhi (220 km, 5-6 hrs)',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:33','2025-03-26 15:55:08','Morning: After breakfast, drive back to Delhi.  Evening: Trip ends in Delhi.'),(348,87,'Day 1: Haridwar → Guptkashi / Sonprayag',NULL,NULL,'2025-03-22 11:46:3